// Zellij config — KDL. Overrides defaults only; any key left unset uses the
// built-in default (Zellij merges this file over its defaults, it doesn't
// replace them).
//
// Dump the full default reference any time with:  zellij setup --dump-config
// Docs: https://zellij.dev/documentation/
//
// Evaluating Zellij as the work organizer over ghostty + tmux.
//
// NON-COLLIDING (unlock-first): `default_mode "locked"` is set at the bottom,
// so Zellij BOOTS LOCKED — every key (Ctrl-p history, Ctrl-t/fzf, Ctrl-h
// backspace, Alt-f word-motion, the tmux Ctrl-b prefix, …) passes straight
// to your shell/programs; nothing is shadowed. Press the leader `Ctrl g` to
// UNLOCK into Normal, drive Zellij with the keys below, then `Ctrl g` again
// to re-lock. This mirrors tmux's one-prefix model. (In Locked mode only
// `Ctrl g` is intercepted.)
//
// ───────────────────────── BASE KEYBINDINGS (v0.44 defaults) ─────────────
// Zellij is MODAL. From the unlocked Normal mode you enter a sub-mode, press
// single keys, then Esc/Enter back to Normal (Ctrl g to re-lock). Current
// mode shows bottom-left in the status bar.
//
// ENTER A MODE (Ctrl g to unlock first) ─ each mode's enter-key also exits it:
//   Ctrl p   Pane          Ctrl t   Tab           Ctrl n   Resize
//   Ctrl h   Move          Ctrl s   Scroll/Search Ctrl o   Session
//   Ctrl g   Locked (ignore all binds; press Ctrl g again to unlock)
//   Ctrl q   Quit Zellij
//
// GLOBAL ─ work in any mode except Locked (no mode switch needed):
//   Alt n            new pane            Alt f         toggle floating panes
//   Alt h/j/k/l      focus pane (or tab at edge, via arrows too)
//   Alt = / Alt -    grow / shrink pane  Alt [ / Alt ] prev / next swap layout
//
// PANE mode (Ctrl p):
//   h/j/k/l move focus   n new   d down-split   r right-split   s stacked
//   x close   f fullscreen   w floating   e embed<->float   z toggle frames
//   c rename   i pin   p cycle focus
//
// TAB mode (Ctrl t):
//   n new   x close   r rename   h/l (or arrows) prev/next   1-9 go to tab N
//   Tab toggle last   s sync-input   b break pane to new tab   [ / ] break L/R
//
// RESIZE mode (Ctrl n):  h/j/k/l grow side · H/J/K/L shrink side · = grow · - shrink
// MOVE mode  (Ctrl h):   h/j/k/l move pane · n/Tab cycle forward · p backward
// SCROLL mode (Ctrl s):  j/k line · Ctrl f/b page · d/u half-page ·
//                        s start search · e edit scrollback in $EDITOR ·
//                        in search: n/p next/prev · c case · w wrap · o whole-word
// SESSION mode (Ctrl o): d detach · w session-manager · c config · p plugin-manager
//
// NESTED tmux: because Zellij stays Locked by default, an attached tmux
//   session inside a Zellij pane receives ALL keys — including its own
//   Ctrl-b prefix. Only `Ctrl g` is intercepted. Unlock only when you want
//   Zellij itself. (This is why unlock-first is the right fit here.)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// Boot in Locked mode → collision-free; `Ctrl g` toggles unlock (see above).
default_mode "locked"
